physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Erythema, edema, warmth, and pain concerning for septic arthritis of the left knee.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Worsened left knee swelling, warmth, and erythema indicated an unresolved infection after initial treatment.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Patient did not appear septic upon returning to the emergency department.
The patient tolerated a graded challenge with dalbavancin without any immediate adverse effects.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: No adverse reactions were reported at the clinic visit a week after discharge.
